Subtitle of Senate Bill 283
TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING UNCLAIMED PROPERTY; AND TO PROVIDE THAT
CERTAIN NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS ARE EXEMPT FROM THE LAW CONCERNING
UNCLAIMED PROPERTY.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 1 to Senate Bill 283
Amend Senate Bill 283 as originally introduced:
Page 1, delete line 36, and substitute the following:
"(b)(1) A nonprofit organization that has an annual revenue of less
than five million dollars ($5,000,000) shall pay, deliver, or cause to be
paid or delivered to the administrator property that has been unclaimed for
one (1) year.
(2) The administrator shall have two (2) years to locate the
apparent owner of the property described under subdivision (b)(1) of this
section.
(3) If the property remains unclaimed after the period described
under subdivision (b)(2) of this section, the property is presumed abandoned
and the administrator shall pay, deliver, or cause to be paid or delivered
the unclaimed property to the nonprofit organization."
AND
